// Plan 159 Ф.1 over-prune hunt: `a + b` on `str` desugars to
// `Nova_str_method_concat(a, b)` (emit_c.rs ~19190, D-R4). The `concat` selector
// is injected by the `+` lowering and never appears syntactically, so without
// seeding it the reachability closure prunes `str.concat` — and `nova_print_str`
// then receives the implicit-int return of an undeclared C function (the exact
// `passing 'int' to parameter of incompatible type 'nova_str'` regression seen
// in plan131/vec_iter_pos). `str.concat` must stay reachable.
// EXPECT_STDOUT a+b+c

module plan159.hunt_str_concat_operator

fn main() {
    ro s = "a" + "+" + "b" + "+" + "c"
    println(s)
}
